  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Report: How normal is the informal sector in Burundi? (Frence language)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is estimated that 95% of Burundians work in the informal economy which includes mainly small-scale agriculture but also services, industry and trade. In the absence of formal jobs, Burundian youth are forced to work in the informal sector. This study provides more insight into the characteristics of the informal sector, the specific opportunities and challenges encountered by informal SME&#x2019;s and the potential gains in formalization. The study helps EKN Burundi and other donors active in the field of PSD to use their interventions more impactfully. It will provide specific recommendations to the new programme Akazi Keza, implemented by SPARK Burundi as part of the Dutch nexus skills-jobs programme as well other EKN-financed programs such as PADANE program of SNV.</narrative>
  </description>
